To obtain the number of occurrences of a specific word, the `std::count_if` function can be used. This method returns the number of elements that meet a given condition and can be applied in this case to count the occurrences of a word in a text file.

To do this, each line of the file would be read and the `std::count_if` function would be applied to each line to count the occurrence of a specific word. For example, if you want to count the occurrences of the term "hello" in a file named "data.txt":

```cpp
#include <fstream>
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <sstream>
#include <iterator>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    // Open the file.
    ifstream file("data.txt");
    if (!file) { // If the file could not be opened, an error message will be displayed.
        cout << "The file cannot be opened.";
        return 1;
    }

    // Read the file until it ends.
    string line;
    while (getline(file, line)) { // Read each line of the file until it ends.
        cout << line << endl; // Display each line of the file on the screen.

        // Count the occurrences of the word "hello" in each line of the file.
        int counter = 0; // Counter for how many times "hello" appears.
        auto it = std::count_if(begin(line), end(line), [&](const auto &c) { return c == "hello"; }); // Check if c is equal to hello and count the number of times "hello" appears in the line string.
        for (auto i = it; i != end(line); ++i) { counter++; } // Count the occurrences of "hello" in each line of the file.

